  "chunks": [
    {
      "chunk_type": "isnad",
      "arabic_text": "أَحْمَدُ بْنُ إِدْرِيسَ عَنْ عِمْرَانَ بْنِ مُوسَى عَنْ هَارُونَ بْنِ مُسْلِمٍ عَنْ مَسْعَدَةَ بْنِ صَدَقَةَ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ قَالَ",
      "translations": {
        "en": "Ahmad ibn Idris, from 'Imran ibn Musa, from Harun ibn Muslim, from Mas'ada ibn Sadaqah, from Abu 'Abdillah عليه السلام, who said:"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "opening",
      "arabic_text": "ذُكِرَتِ التَّقِيَّةُ يَوْمًا عِنْدَ عَلِيِّ بْنِ الْحُسَيْنِ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ فَقَالَ وَاللَّهِ لَوْ عَلِمَ أَبُو ذَرٍّ مَا فِي قَلْبِ سَلْمَانَ لَقَتَلَهُ وَقَدْ آخَى رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صَلَّى اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ بَيْنَهُمَا.",
      "translations": {
        "en": "Taqiyyah was mentioned one day in the presence of 'Ali ibn al-Husayn عليه السلام, so he said: “By Allah, if Abu Dharr knew what was in the heart of Salman, he would have killed him, while the Messenger of Allah صلى الله عليه وآله had established brotherhood between the two of them.”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "body",
      "arabic_text": "فَمَا ظَنُّكُمْ بِسَائِرِ الْخَلْقِ؟ إِنَّ عِلْمَ الْعُلَمَاءِ صَعْبٌ مُسْتَصْعَبٌ، لَا يَحْتَمِلُهُ إِلَّا نَبِيٌّ مُرْسَلٌ أَوْ مَلَكٌ مُقَرَّبٌ أَوْ عَبْدٌ مُؤْمِنٌ امْتَحَنَ اللَّهُ قَلْبَهُ لِلْإِيمَانِ.",
      "translations": {
        "en": "So what do you think about the rest of creation? The knowledge of the scholars is difficult and made difficult; none can bear it except a sent Prophet, or a near Angel, or a believing servant whose heart Allah has tested for faith.”
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "closing",
      "arabic_text": "فَقَالَ: وَإِنَّمَا صَارَ سَلْمَانُ مِنَ الْعُلَمَاءِ لِأَنَّهُ امْرُؤٌ مِنَّا أَهْلَ الْبَيْتِ، فَلِذَلِكَ نَسَبْتُهُ إِلَى الْعُلَمَاءِ.",
      "translations": {
        "en": "Then he said: “Salman only became one of the scholars because he is a man from us, Ahl al-Bayt; therefore, for that reason I have attributed him to the scholars.”"
      }
    }
  ],
  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "summary": "This hadith emphasizes that the deeper realities of the knowledge of the Ahl al-Bayt عليهم السلام are difficult to bear and are not accessible to everyone. It also highlights the lofty rank of Salman by attributing him to Ahl al-Bayt and counting him among the true knowers. The narration is significant in showing both the principle of taqiyyah and the exclusivity and weight of sacred knowledge.",
      "seo_question": "Why does the hadith say that the knowledge of the Ahl al-Bayt is difficult to bear, and what is Salman’s special rank?",
      "key_terms": {
        "التَّقِيَّةُ": "prudent dissimulation in circumstances requiring concealment",
        "عِلْمَ": "knowledge, specifically the profound knowledge referred to in the hadith",
        "الْعُلَمَاءِ": "the knowledgeable ones, those possessing elevated sacred knowledge",
        "مُسْتَصْعَبٌ": "made exceedingly difficult and hard to bear",
        "مُؤْمِنٌ": "a believing servant",
        "امْتَحَنَ": "tested and proven",
        "الْإِيمَانِ": "faith",
        "أَهْلَ الْبَيْتِ": "the People of the Household of the Prophet صلى الله عليه وآله"
      }
    }
  },
